    <p>If you haven't successfully programmed your Arduino yet, go back to the
      blink sketch and make it happen.</p>
    In the Arduino IDE, set up the hardware:
    <ul>
      <li>Tools-&gt;Board-&gt;Arduino Nano</li>
      <li>Tools-&gt;Processor-&gt;Atmega328P (Old Bootloader)</li>
      <li>Tools-&gt;Port-&gt; whatever port appears in this list when you plug
        in the Arduino</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Download, modify, compile and upload the sketch</p>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="https://github.com/KnoxMakers/Electronics/tree/master/UltiBadge/example_code/i2c_scanner">Download
          i2c_bus_scanner.ino</a> from the KnoxMakers Github</li>
      <li>Watch the Adruino IDE serial monitor for reports back during testing
        (Tools-&gt;Serial Monitor)</li>
      <li>Compile, upload and enjoy!</li>
    </ul>
    <br>
